item.title: Shares tumble as jobless rate worsens
item.description: Australian stocks slid on Thursday amid signs rising unemployment could weaken the Australian economy.

item.title: Accused strangler’s chilling prison letters
item.description: A man who allegedly abused his ex-partner and strangled her until she went limp will stay behind bars after sending the woman almost 100 pages of letters while in prison.

item.title: Man shot by cops after ‘frenzied attack’
item.description: A man is dead after being shot by police who arrived on the scene of a brutal, “frenzied attack” on a woman in Melbourne’s northwest this afternoon.

item.title: Medibank slapped with $5m fine
item.description: Major health insurance provider Medibank Private has been slapped with a multimillion-dollar fine for making misleading claims about benefits cover to members.

item.title: Tigers call on Benji to extend career
item.description: Wests Tigers players have urged Benji Marshall to extend his stellar career for another season, declaring the Tigers fan favourite still trains like a teenager.

item.title: ‘You’re only 14’: Instructor’s sick post
item.description: A 65-year-old former driving instructor who sent explicit sexual messages to a cop he thought was a teenage girl before arranging to meet up for sex will spend at least nine months in prison.

item.title: Why teen stabbed his grandad to death
item.description: A teenage boy who killed his grandfather for being “creepy” will spend a maximum of 16 years in prison.

item.title: Suspicious house fire in dramatic video
item.description: A dramatic video has been released by Queensland Police of flames engulfing a home in northern Rockhampton overnight.

item.title: Jobless rate highest in 22 years
item.description: Australia has recorded the highest unemployment rate for 22 years, raising fears the “COVID-19 economic recession” will dampen prospects of an early recovery.

item.title: Victorians cop $1m in virus fines
item.description: Victorians have chalked up more than $1 million worth of fines since the coronavirus lockdown was reinstated a week ago.
